WEBVTT

00:01.201 --> 00:02.534
I'm Letty.
- Javier.

00:02.536 --> 00:03.369
Cheers.

00:03.371 --> 00:04.370
[ Moans ]

00:04.372 --> 00:06.305
There's a man
coming here to kill you.

00:06.307 --> 00:08.774
You have a shotgun
pointed at your back.

00:08.776 --> 00:10.542
I want to see Jacob.

00:10.544 --> 00:12.864
You're violating
your restraining order
just standing there.

00:13.680 --> 00:17.049
What are you doing?
Call it an advance.

00:17.051 --> 00:18.150
No!

00:18.152 --> 00:20.152
You work for me now.

00:20.154 --> 00:21.887
I saved your life!

00:21.889 --> 00:23.455
Thank you, my prince.

00:23.457 --> 00:25.524
I'm so glad
to be alive right now

00:25.526 --> 00:27.726
with a murderer,
two dead bodies,
and no way out.

00:27.728 --> 00:30.529
I can't thank you enough
for rescuing me.

00:30.531 --> 00:31.964
Javier:
He looks like you.

00:31.966 --> 00:33.165
I want to get him back.

00:33.167 --> 00:34.233
I think you can.

00:34.235 --> 00:36.068
If you stop screwing up.

00:36.070 --> 00:37.836
I'm trying.

00:37.838 --> 00:39.405
Try harder.

00:39.407 --> 00:41.407
You really are a stalker.
You know that.

00:41.409 --> 00:42.908
Now I've covered for you twice.

00:42.910 --> 00:44.343
[ Through cellphone ]
I don't know where you are,

00:44.345 --> 00:46.311
but you will
be in my office tomorrow.

00:46.313 --> 00:48.647
I don't have your phone number.

00:51.084 --> 00:52.785
I'm not giving you
my phone number.

00:56.923 --> 00:58.557
[ Doorbells jingle ]

00:58.559 --> 01:01.060
<i>[ Country music playing softly</i>
<i>through speaker ]</i>

01:01.062 --> 01:03.695
[ Plates rattling ]

01:03.697 --> 01:08.467
[ Plate scraping ]

01:12.272 --> 01:14.339
Javier: I can drive you
to Asheville.

01:19.012 --> 01:21.413
Letty: I know you can.

01:26.619 --> 01:29.955
I'll... I'll just put it
in your phone, okay?

01:29.957 --> 01:31.356
So if you get into trouble...

01:31.358 --> 01:33.759
You're not touching my phone.

01:33.761 --> 01:36.462
You can write it down.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.567
[ Sighs ]

01:41.569 --> 01:44.970
I don't...
I don't have any paper.

01:44.972 --> 01:47.840
[ Insects chirping ]

02:05.992 --> 02:08.994
Do I have to keep worrying?

02:08.996 --> 02:11.663
About our road trip?

02:11.665 --> 02:14.333
About<i> you.</i>

02:14.335 --> 02:18.537
I told you.
We're good.

02:20.573 --> 02:22.508
Good.

02:25.912 --> 02:27.746
[ Door handle clicks ]

02:48.768 --> 02:51.436
[ Door opens ]

02:53.940 --> 02:57.843
<i>[ Indistinct chatter</i>
<i>over P.A. ]</i>

03:01.681 --> 03:04.383
[ Engine revs ]

03:12.959 --> 03:15.394
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

03:15.396 --> 03:18.197
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

03:18.199 --> 03:20.365
♪ Before you do something ♪

03:20.367 --> 03:22.968
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

03:22.970 --> 03:25.571
♪ Bricks are caving in ♪

03:25.573 --> 03:27.973
♪ Oh, how sweet this sin ♪

03:27.975 --> 03:30.576
♪ I left you the keys ♪

03:30.578 --> 03:32.978
♪ You won't let me in ♪

03:32.980 --> 03:35.380
♪ Hard time forgiving ♪

03:35.382 --> 03:38.150
♪ Even harder forgetting ♪

03:38.152 --> 03:40.419
♪ Before you do something ♪

03:40.421 --> 03:43.755
♪ You might regret, friend ♪

03:43.757 --> 03:46.258
♪ Time to make the club go up ♪

03:46.260 --> 03:48.260
♪ Time to shut this bitch down ♪

03:48.262 --> 03:50.229
♪ This is not how I woke up ♪

03:50.231 --> 03:52.231
♪ But it's how I look now ♪

03:52.233 --> 03:54.166
♪ If you leave with me ♪

03:54.168 --> 03:56.168
♪ We'll be on till morn ♪

03:56.170 --> 03:58.070
♪ Then we rinse and repeat ♪

03:58.072 --> 04:00.172
♪ And it just goes on ♪

04:00.174 --> 04:01.240
Where you been?

04:01.242 --> 04:02.608
Really?

04:02.610 --> 04:03.875
Thought I'd try.

04:03.877 --> 04:04.910
Don't try.

04:04.912 --> 04:06.678
I'm gonna make a suggestion.

04:06.680 --> 04:07.779
Okay.

04:07.781 --> 04:10.682
How about you stop
being such an asshole?

04:10.684 --> 04:11.950
Sure.

04:11.952 --> 04:14.286
I'll put it on my to-do list
right under "join the gym."

04:14.288 --> 04:15.587
Don't do that.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.556
Don't pretend
like you don't care.

04:17.558 --> 04:19.424
You're so used
to disappointing people,

04:19.426 --> 04:20.759
it doesn't affect you anymore,

04:20.761 --> 04:23.128
but disappointing people
and being an asshole

04:23.130 --> 04:24.196
are two different things.

04:24.198 --> 04:26.465
So uplifting, always.

04:26.467 --> 04:28.800
Thank you.
I get that a lot.

04:28.802 --> 04:31.970
I'm fine.

04:31.972 --> 04:33.739
I didn't do anything wrong.

04:33.741 --> 04:36.908
I'm sorry for being an asshole.

04:36.910 --> 04:38.610
I'm trying to do better.

04:38.612 --> 04:42.214
I got stuck in a bad situation
and I got myself out of it.

04:42.216 --> 04:45.651
A situation with a guy who
didn't let you use, you said.

04:45.653 --> 04:46.752
I did.

04:46.754 --> 04:48.487
Sounds like
a really bad situation.

04:48.489 --> 04:51.823
It was.
- We're no good for each other.

04:51.825 --> 04:53.659
Letty.

04:53.661 --> 04:55.394
Christian.

04:55.396 --> 05:00.365
Being connected to other
human beings is important.

05:00.367 --> 05:01.667
You need people in your life

05:01.669 --> 05:04.569
who care about you,
who you care about.

05:06.339 --> 05:08.740
I'm going
to my high-school reunion.

05:08.742 --> 05:10.642
You didn't graduate
high school.

05:10.644 --> 05:13.478
And I got the Facebook
invitation anyway.

05:14.814 --> 05:17.683
This wouldn't happen to be
about your son, would it?

05:17.685 --> 05:18.917
No.

05:18.919 --> 05:21.286
You know you can't go
anywhere near him, Letty.

05:21.288 --> 05:22.921
I'm not going near him.

05:22.923 --> 05:26.191
I'm going to my high-school
reunion Saturday night

05:26.193 --> 05:28.260
to make some human connections.

05:28.262 --> 05:30.429
Mm-hmm.

05:30.431 --> 05:32.030
What about getting a job?

05:32.032 --> 05:37.536
Yes, I want to get a job,
a normal place to live...

05:37.538 --> 05:39.671
all the things.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.873
Good.

05:41.875 --> 05:45.944
That's what everybody
keeps telling me.

05:45.946 --> 05:50.982
And, uh... you went
to high school where, exactly?

05:50.984 --> 05:52.517
Danville High.

05:52.519 --> 05:56.021
It's within state lines,
but it's kind of far away.

05:56.023 --> 05:58.123
So, I guess that means

05:58.125 --> 06:01.126
that you'll be missing
your check-in on Saturday.

06:01.128 --> 06:03.695
I can do Monday or Tuesday.

06:03.697 --> 06:06.231
Mm-hmm.

06:06.233 --> 06:08.900
I want photographic evidence

06:08.902 --> 06:11.136
of you
at this high-school reunion.

06:11.138 --> 06:14.072
Oh, I will selfie up a storm.

06:14.074 --> 06:15.907
[ Sighs ]

06:15.909 --> 06:19.211
♪♪

06:19.213 --> 06:20.879
♪ And it just goes on ♪

06:24.350 --> 06:26.752
[ Horn honks ]

06:31.090 --> 06:32.891
Hi.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.426
Hi.

06:34.428 --> 06:36.928
Well, well.
Freedom looks good on you.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.497
Did you put your face
all over the car

06:38.499 --> 06:40.165
before or after
- You got it bulletproofed?

06:40.167 --> 06:41.600
Nice bag.

06:41.602 --> 06:43.068
Wait, don't tell me...
Chinatown.

06:43.070 --> 06:44.770
Did you get
- Your tramp stamp removed,

06:44.772 --> 06:46.605
or is that J.Crew number
just thick enough

06:46.607 --> 06:48.006
to cover it up?

06:48.008 --> 06:49.241
It's cashmere.

06:49.243 --> 06:50.742
It's nice.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.177
Get in.

06:54.947 --> 06:57.115
It is so good to see you.
It really is.

06:57.117 --> 06:58.617
It is good to see<i> you.</i>

06:58.619 --> 07:00.519
The real-estate thing
seems like it's working out.

07:00.521 --> 07:01.920
God, it's booming.

07:01.922 --> 07:04.256
I've already sold three houses
so far this month.

07:04.258 --> 07:05.457
Don't tell him I told you,

07:05.459 --> 07:07.459
but I'm making more
than Kyle now.

07:07.461 --> 07:08.860
Work!
- [ Laughs ]

07:08.862 --> 07:09.795
[ Chuckles ]

07:09.797 --> 07:12.264
[ Exhales ]
Let's go get a drink.

07:12.266 --> 07:15.100
I want to hear everything.

07:15.102 --> 07:16.902
I don't drink.

07:16.904 --> 07:17.936
What?

07:17.938 --> 07:20.405
On weekdays.
- I don't drink on weekdays.

07:20.407 --> 07:22.641
Right, me neither.

07:25.044 --> 07:27.813
Anyway, we're having a barbecue
at the house later tonight

07:27.815 --> 07:29.781
for the reunion-planning
committee.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.416
It's a stupid
final-meeting thing.

07:31.418 --> 07:32.751
It's at 6:00.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.886
I love that you're
- On the planning committee.

07:34.888 --> 07:36.755
I love that you're coming
to the reunion.

07:36.757 --> 07:37.989
How many points do I get

07:37.991 --> 07:40.258
for using a high-school reunion
as an alibi?

07:40.260 --> 07:41.626
10.
[ Chuckles ]

07:41.628 --> 07:43.462
10?
At least 100.

07:43.464 --> 07:44.729
10 out of 10.

07:44.731 --> 07:46.998
10 is... ultimately,
10 is a low number.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.133
[ Chuckles ]

07:50.169 --> 07:52.971
So, aren't you supposed to,
like, never drink?

07:52.973 --> 07:54.506
Yeah.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.677
So boring.

07:59.846 --> 08:01.913
Yeah, but I mean,
- If you're really gonna try

08:01.915 --> 08:04.182
to come back here
and start over,

08:04.184 --> 08:05.517
try to get Jacob,

08:05.519 --> 08:07.452
which I think is a great plan,
by the way...

08:07.454 --> 08:09.421
and Kyle is totally down
to help you

08:09.423 --> 08:10.989
with all the legal stuff.

08:12.792 --> 08:17.128
But, I mean, you know,
you probably should never drink.

08:17.130 --> 08:20.165
Probably not.

08:20.167 --> 08:23.702
So, how's it work with Jacob,
exactly?

08:23.704 --> 08:25.871
You can't come within how far
of him?

08:25.873 --> 08:27.205
1,000 feet.

08:27.207 --> 08:29.207
How are you supposed to know
how far 1,000 feet is?

08:29.209 --> 08:30.509
I don't know.

08:30.511 --> 08:32.143
How is that different
from 500 feet?

08:32.145 --> 08:34.546
I mean, you're not even really
near the child at 100 feet.

08:34.548 --> 08:36.481
Some people can't help
but do damage,

08:36.483 --> 08:37.883
even at 100 feet.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.218
What damage are you gonna do
at 100 feet?

08:40.220 --> 08:42.387
[ Scoffs ] I don't know.

08:42.389 --> 08:45.524
Well, I think 1,000 feet
is excessive,

08:45.526 --> 08:48.059
but you probably
should wait in the car.

08:48.061 --> 08:49.528
For what?

08:49.530 --> 08:51.897
We're picking up
Autumn and Dax.

08:51.899 --> 08:53.698
Jacob goes to the same school.

08:57.003 --> 08:58.570
Just got to run in and sign

08:58.572 --> 09:02.040
this stupid permission-slip
thing for Dax.

09:08.814 --> 09:11.316
Woman: What the hell?

09:12.585 --> 09:14.553
1,000 feet.
- I'm just here with Tiffany.

09:14.555 --> 09:15.854
She's picking up her kids.

09:15.856 --> 09:17.656
As soon as the bell rings,
I'll get in the car.

09:17.658 --> 09:19.925
The windows are tinted.
Jacob won't even see me.

09:19.927 --> 09:23.495
You're just here
with Tiffany Dash Real Estate?

09:23.497 --> 09:25.230
I'm staying with her.
Why?

09:26.732 --> 09:29.534
Our class reunion
is this weekend.

09:29.536 --> 09:33.071
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God.

09:35.374 --> 09:36.775
Truth.

09:36.777 --> 09:38.677
Trying to make a normal life,
Mom.

09:38.679 --> 09:40.111
Get a job, get my own place.

09:40.113 --> 09:43.248
Tiffany's gonna help me
look for something.

09:43.250 --> 09:47.852
Happy house hunt.

09:48.955 --> 09:51.790
Are you gonna say anything about
the money I left?

09:53.259 --> 09:54.459
What money?

09:54.461 --> 09:56.428
In the mailbox.

09:56.430 --> 09:57.963
What?

09:57.965 --> 10:01.533
I left $20,000 in the mailbox.

10:01.535 --> 10:02.767
I have no idea
- What you're talking about.

10:02.769 --> 10:06.071
For Jacob.
Are you serious?

10:06.073 --> 10:08.640
Why would you leave that much
money in a mailbox, Letty?

10:08.642 --> 10:11.009
Oh, my God.

10:15.481 --> 10:17.482
Oh, you're such a bitch.

10:17.484 --> 10:19.818
It was very generous of you.

10:19.820 --> 10:24.322
Jacob has a new wardrobe
and $19,000 in a college fund.

10:24.324 --> 10:26.424
He has a college fund?

10:26.426 --> 10:28.593
Yeah, he does now.

10:28.595 --> 10:30.428
[ School bell rings ]

10:30.430 --> 10:31.796
Why don't you just get back

10:31.798 --> 10:35.000
in Tiffany's limo
or whatever that is?

10:36.636 --> 10:39.004
Can we have dinner?

10:39.006 --> 10:40.939
What?

10:40.941 --> 10:43.908
Dinner.
You and me.

10:43.910 --> 10:47.078
As long as you're buying.

10:47.080 --> 10:51.182
[ Children
shouting indistinctly ]

11:05.264 --> 11:09.167
♪♪

11:17.376 --> 11:21.246
♪♪

11:32.958 --> 11:34.459
Tom:<i> Clear tonight,</i>
<i>with a low of 81.</i>

11:34.461 --> 11:35.827
<i>Tomorrow,</i>
<i>looks like more sunshine</i>

11:35.829 --> 11:36.961
<i>and slightly warmer</i>
<i>temperatures.</i>

11:36.963 --> 11:38.196
Female Reporter:
<i>Thanks, Tom.</i>

11:38.198 --> 11:39.631
<i>I'm here now with Melanie,</i>

11:39.633 --> 11:41.633
<i>who recently encountered</i>
<i>a suspicious couple.</i>

11:41.635 --> 11:43.001
<i>Can you tell us</i>
<i>what they looked like?</i>

11:43.003 --> 11:45.036
Melanie:<i> Absolutely.</i>
<i>Yeah, he was hot.</i>

11:45.038 --> 11:46.538
<i>He was like a seven</i>
<i>or an eight.</i>
- [ Television volume increases ]

11:46.540 --> 11:48.206
<i>Or even...</i>
<i>maybe even a nine.</i>

11:48.208 --> 11:49.541
<i>Uh, he's Mexican.</i>

11:49.543 --> 11:51.209
<i>He had that accent, definitely.</i>

11:51.211 --> 11:53.645
<i>And she had red hair</i>
<i>like up to here.</i>

11:53.647 --> 11:55.246
Very<i> pretty.</i>

11:55.248 --> 11:58.383
<i>They are possible suspects</i>
<i>in the case of a missing couple</i>

11:58.385 --> 12:00.952
<i>who were last seen</i>
- <i>At The Inn at Trousdale Farm,</i>

12:00.954 --> 12:03.154
[Muffled, echoing]<i> an upscale</i>
<i>hotel in the Smoky Mountains,</i>

12:03.156 --> 12:05.490
<i>where authorities continue</i>
<i>to seek information</i>

12:05.492 --> 12:07.759
<i>from guests and employees.</i>

12:07.761 --> 12:09.394
<i>Anyone with information</i>
<i>about their whereabouts</i>

12:09.396 --> 12:11.730
<i>should contact</i>
<i>local authorities.</i>
[ Knock on door ]

12:11.732 --> 12:13.398
[ Television shuts off ]

12:13.400 --> 12:16.167
Mom said to come get you
for the barbecue.

12:16.169 --> 12:18.737
Thanks, Autumn.

12:19.538 --> 12:23.208
<i>[ Mid-tempo music playing</i>
<i>through speaker ]</i>

12:23.210 --> 12:27.112
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:29.081 --> 12:31.349
Oh, I bet you're Letty.

12:31.351 --> 12:33.218
Yeah. Hi.

12:33.220 --> 12:34.252
I'm Azalea.

12:34.254 --> 12:35.587
Uh, we never met at DHS

12:35.589 --> 12:37.455
because my family moved here
when I was a junior,

12:37.457 --> 12:39.023
and I think
you were gone by then.

12:39.025 --> 12:39.958
Right.

12:39.960 --> 12:42.393
Tiffany talks about you
all the time.

12:42.395 --> 12:44.362
It is so nice
to finally meet you.

12:44.364 --> 12:46.631
Give it time.
- [ Chuckles ]
I always do.

12:46.633 --> 12:49.400
Uh, I know about
your situation.

12:49.402 --> 12:51.035
Really?

12:51.037 --> 12:53.438
I had a cousin who struggled
with addiction.

12:53.440 --> 12:55.540
He also lost his child.

12:55.542 --> 12:57.942
I'm sorry to hear that.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.111
Did Tiffany tell you
about my situation?

13:00.113 --> 13:02.213
She's a very good friend
to you.

13:02.215 --> 13:04.783
And I'd love to be
a good friend, too.

13:04.785 --> 13:07.585
Would you like
- To be my guest this Sunday?

13:07.587 --> 13:09.454
Where?
- Church.

13:09.456 --> 13:13.324
God's dead, Azalea.

13:18.898 --> 13:20.999
[ Echoing bottles clink ]

13:22.468 --> 13:25.637
[ Echoing laughing ]

13:25.639 --> 13:27.806
[ Echoing stops ]
"God's dead, Azalea."

13:27.808 --> 13:29.274
[ Chuckling ] Hey, Kyle.

13:29.276 --> 13:31.309
Hi.

13:31.311 --> 13:33.111
Man, I've really missed
having you around

13:33.113 --> 13:35.079
to say all the shit
I wish I came up with.

13:35.081 --> 13:36.147
[ Chuckles ]

13:36.149 --> 13:38.616
"God's dead, Azalea."
That was... good.

13:38.618 --> 13:40.485
It's good to see you.
[ Chuckles ]

13:40.487 --> 13:41.820
You, too.

13:41.822 --> 13:43.822
Oh, I thought that
you might want a soda.

13:43.824 --> 13:45.190
Oh.
- Ginger ale okay?

13:45.192 --> 13:46.825
If not,
- We got lots of other kinds.

13:46.827 --> 13:49.427
No, it's very good.
Thank you.

13:49.429 --> 13:51.129
[ Soda tab pops ]

13:51.131 --> 13:55.300
Hey, Tiffany said you
might be able to help
me out with Jacob.

13:55.302 --> 13:58.136
Yeah. I'll do everything
I can, obviously.

13:58.138 --> 14:00.171
You need to be able to show
that you have a job.

14:00.173 --> 14:01.406
I know that for sure.

14:01.408 --> 14:04.008
I have an interview
at a temp agency tomorrow.

14:04.010 --> 14:05.643
The one on Wrightsville?
- The one.

14:05.645 --> 14:06.945
My office is right there.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.546
Come by after,
- We'll go through everything.

14:08.548 --> 14:10.782
Are you any good?

14:10.784 --> 14:14.185
Medium.
[ Clears throat ]

14:14.187 --> 14:15.353
[ Chuckles ]

14:15.355 --> 14:17.355
Cheers.
- Cheers.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.424
[ Water running ]

14:25.831 --> 14:29.000
Javier: So proud of us.
We had a barbecue.

14:29.002 --> 14:31.202
♪♪

14:34.707 --> 14:37.709
I kicked everybody out.

14:37.711 --> 14:40.178
Tiffany:
You don't have to clean up.

14:40.180 --> 14:41.646
[ Pot clatters ]

14:42.982 --> 14:46.751
Does this scream "hire me"
or what?

14:46.753 --> 14:48.219
It screams something.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.822
It's perfect for an interview.
It's classic.

14:50.824 --> 14:52.357
I have clothes.

14:52.359 --> 14:53.725
Okay.

14:53.727 --> 14:56.060
Well, I'll put it on your bed
just in case.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.528
Wouldn't fit me anymore,
anyway.

14:57.530 --> 14:58.730
I've gained so much weight.

14:58.732 --> 15:00.498
You have not.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.666
You're such a liar.

15:01.668 --> 15:04.068
If I can't drink or get high,

15:04.070 --> 15:06.271
at least I can hang on
to my lying.

15:06.273 --> 15:07.805
